comments.body:


The following is an error logged for the Elements application:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/c25caaee-f189-483d-9336-ecc6861ab5a9)

This error message might also well be related:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/94bd8996-1f89-441f-ba25-2dc85c2763a1)

I am not currently aware of the role of the server `sdp202w`, and I will enquire about this using SN@P.
The SN@P ticket is currently awaiting a response at https://princeton.service-now.com/service?id=ticket&table=incident&sys_id=40d6fb65879809549cd197183cbb3501&view=sp

After further trying to reproduce and diagnose this error, the following has been achieved:

- The Elements scheduler service has been manually restarted (it appears to not have been running)
- A more detailed error message has been located

Reviewing the stack trace, this seems to be somehow related to some issues affecting an XML caching pipeline (raising https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.collections.generic.keynotfoundexception?view=net-6.0). As Elements is not an open source code base, I am going to proceed with contacting Symplectic Support.
https://support.symplectic.co.uk/support/tickets/359356 has been used to request support with this issue.

Following the discussion from Symplectic Support, the following may explain why this failure occurred:

> Can you tell us more about what happened after you attempted to upgrade last week? The error you sent is frequently (though not always) caused by the version of the deployed application binaries not being aligned with the version of the database. This can be caused by attempting to manually fix problems with a failed upgrade instead of rolling back and trying again.

After reviewing the Nagios server alerts for cisdr201w, the following was found:

```
***** Nagios Monitor XI Alert *****

Notification Type: PROBLEM

Service: prod: user: web: https_oaworkflow
Host: cisdr201w.princeton.edu
Address: cisdr201w.princeton.edu
State: CRITICAL

Date/Time: Tue Dec 7 10:46:18 EST 2021

Additional Info:

HTTP CRITICAL: HTTP/1.1 500 Internal Server Error - string CAS Login not found on https://oaworkflow.princeton.edu:443/login.html - 5416 bytes in 0.112 second response time
```

Prior to this message, there were no failures in the production server environment. This confirms my suspicion that this was not immediately triggered by the failed upgrade attempt undertaken on 12/01/2021.

https://princeton.service-now.com/service?id=ticket&table=incident&sys_id=1c3da87d87d449549cd197183cbb355a&view=sp was created in order to assist with providing additional information to Symplectic support specialists.

Trying to use the Microsoft Management Console to retrieve more detailed logs yields the following:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/6735b2cb-a439-4a1c-9e07-8b006f76eb7b)

Hi, Jay.

1) These are the shibboleth attributes we need:
"SHIB_netid"

"SHIB_department"

"SHIB_major"
"SHIB_gradYear"
"SHIB_gradMonth"
"SHIB_orcid"

2) We are already using SSL for connection, so I don't think we need to further encrypt the traffic, but I am happy to follow OIT's guidance here.

3) The Login can be tested at https://vireo-staging.princeton.edu/Shibboleth.sso/Login

Thank you!
Bess Sadler
Closing because something went wrong with the rebase here, and a 4-line change ballooned to 44 commits changing 138 files. See #2600 for a clean PR with this same content.
